                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since the fix for 455, I&apos;ve found a problem. Oracle has a NUMBER &lt;br/&gt;
column type, which may be specified with sizes, eg:  NUMBER(7),&lt;br/&gt;
or NUMBER(9,3), but may also be unsized,  eg: NUMBER. Since the&lt;br/&gt;
fix for 455, the new code is failing to  process the &quot;NUMBER&lt;/p&gt;
{0}&quot; template&lt;br/&gt;
for non-sized  columns, so the DDL sent to the DBMS is like: &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
CREATE TABLE ABSTRACTMAPPEDAPPIDSUPER ( ..., VERSN NUMBER{0}
&lt;p&gt;, ... &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;which needless to say, dies. &lt;/p&gt;

